comments: McBride (NYK) reaches in and initiates contact to Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) arm that affects his ability to maintain possession of the ball at the end of the drive.
Dort (OKC) establishes himself in DiVincenzo's (NYK) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Brunson (NYK) legally contests Williams' (OKC) jump shot attempt.
Hart (NYK) gathers the pass on his right foot and takes two steps before making a pass attempt.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) makes contact with the ball last as he deflects the pass from Hart (NYK) out of bounds. NYK correctly maintain possession.
Hartenstein (NYK) establishes himself in Williams' (OKC) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Giddy (OKC) delivers contact to DiVincenzo's (NYK) body as he gains possession of the rebound.
Williams (OKC) brings his off-arm toward DiVincenzo (NYK) and marginal contact occurs as Williams (OKC) releases away without applying any force.
DiVincenzo (NYK) grabs Williams' (OKC) arm and initiates contact on the perimeter.
DiVincenzo (NYK) brings his hands toward Williams (OKC) and marginal contact occurs as DiVincenzo (NYK) releases away during the play.
Wallace (OKC) legally contests Brunson's (NYK) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Holmgren (OKC) is last to make contact with ball before it goes out of bounds. NYK correctly maintains possession.
Hartenstein (NYK) establishes himself in Dort's (OKC) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Brunson (NYK) does not bring two hands to the ball during his drive.
Holmgren (OKC) initiates contact to Brunson's (NYK) off arm which affects his driving shot attempt.
Dort (OKC) contests DiVincenzo's (NYK) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) is last to make contact with the ball before it goes out of bounds. NYK correctly maintains possession.
Dort (OKC) jumps to contest Brunson's (NYK) shot, and following contact by Hartenstein (NYK) on Dort, Dort makes incidental contact with Brunson after the shot is released.
McBride (NYK) legally contests Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) jump shot attempt.
Hartenstein (NYK) establishes himself in Wallace's (OKC) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) legally contests Brunson's (NYK) jump shot attempt.
